    <div class="tg-hero__inner">
      <span class="tg-hero__type">Study Guide · 5 Sessions</span>
      <h1 class="tg-hero__title">The Sermon on the Mount</h1>
      <p class="tg-hero__intro">
        Matthew 5–7 is the fullest account of Jesus's teaching in any of the Gospels. It is not
        a new law to replace Moses but a disclosure of what kingdom life looks like from the
        inside — the ethics that follow naturally from the good news that the kingdom has arrived.
        This guide works through each major section, asking what Jesus demands and why.
      </p>
      <blockquote class="tg-hero__key-verse">
        <p>Blessed are the poor in spirit, for theirs is the kingdom of heaven.</p>
        <cite><a class="ref" data-ref="Matthew 5:3">Matthew 5:3</a></cite>
      </blockquote>
    </div>
